      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " فِي امْرَأَةٍ لَهَا زَوْجٌ مَمْلُوكٌ فَمَاتَ مَوْلَاهُ فَوَرِثَتْهُ قَالَ لَيْسَ بَيْنَهُمَا نِكَاحٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Sayf Bin Ameyra and Muhammad Bin Abu Hamza, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said regarding a woman for whom there was a slave husband. So his master died, and she inherited him. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no marriage between the two of them’."
        ]
      }
